  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel the<strong> potatoes</strong> and chop them into chunky chips, then add them to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 6-8 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617708271498-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617708271498-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617708271498-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617708271498-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617708271498-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>to a deep baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until the oil is hot</p><p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Combine the<strong> chopped shallot</strong> with the <strong>mayo</strong> and the juice of 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span> <strong>lemon </strong>in a small bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good stir – this is your <strong>lemon mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617708285776-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617708285776-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617708285776-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617708285776-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617708285776-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, drain the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>chunky chips </strong>and reserve the pot, give them a shake in the colander until the edges have fluffed up a little</p><p>Carefully remove the baking tray of hot oil from the oven and add the <strong>fluffed chunky chips</strong></p><p>Season them with <strong>salt </strong>and turn them a few times until they're fully coated in the oil</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617708305798-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617708305798-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617708305798-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617708305798-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617708305798-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the<strong> Marmite</strong> and 80ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [160ml] </span><strong>very cold water </strong>in a small bowl,<strong> </strong>stirring continuously until fully combined – this is your <strong>Marmite water</strong></p><p>Add 60g <span class=\"text-danger\">[120g] </span><strong>flour</strong> to a separate large bowl with <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!), a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the<strong> Marmite water</strong></p><p>Stir everything together thoroughly until there are no lumps, then set aside for later – this is your <strong>batter</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1617708319476-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1617708319476-x400.jpg",
